<workout_file>
  <author>Gravel God Training</author>
  <name>W01 Tue - FTP Test</name>
  <description>• STRUCTURE:
  • 20 min warmup with progressive intensity
  • 5 min all-out effort
  • 10 min recovery
  • 20 min max sustained effort
  • 10 min cooldown

  • Classic FTP test.
  • 5-min all-out primes the system.
  • Then 20-min sustained max effort (not sprint, controlled).
  • Average watts × 0.95 = FTP.
  • This sets your training zones.
  • CRITICAL: In polarized training, Z1-Z2 (55-75% FTP) is easy, Z4-Z5+ (95%+ FTP) is hard.
  • Z3 (76-94% FTP) is avoided except in short transitions.
  • Write down your FTP.</description>
  <sportType>bike</sportType>
      <workout>
    <Warmup Duration="1200" PowerLow="0.50" PowerHigh="0.75"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="300" Power="1.20"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="600" Power="0.55"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="1200" Power="1.05"/>
    <Cooldown Duration="600" PowerLow="0.70" PowerHigh="0.50"/>
  </workout>
</workout_file>